						<description>Caliber: 40x46mm. 1-round tube. Single shot.					
The M203 is a single shot grenade launcher that was designed to be mounted to various rifles (although standalone variants exist.) First created in the late 1960s, versions made specifically for earlier rifles (such as the M16 and Diemaco C7) were adapted with special handguards, as the M203 attached directly to the barrel on two points. Later versions (dubbed "M203A2") made in the 2000s were adapted to fit on the railed handguards used by contemporary rifles, needing only one point of attachment to the rifle's barrel.</description>
